<?xml-model href="https://docs.longlink.dev/schema.xsd" schematypens="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"?>
<Page name="Example" icon="layout-grid">
  <State id="exampleForm" fullName="" email="" notes="" subscribed="true" notifications="false" progress="35" status="open" priority='[2,4]'>
    <Query id="example" path="/example">
      <p>Fetched title: {example.title}</p>
      <p>Subscribed: {exampleForm.subscribed}</p>
      <Button action="/example" method="POST" payload='{"title":"{exampleForm.fullName}"}' invalidate="example" variant="default" size="sm">
        Refetch example
      </Button>
      <Input value="$exampleForm.fullName" placeholder="Ada Lovelace" />
      <Input value="$exampleForm.email" placeholder="ada@example.com" />
      <Input value="2026-05-05" />
      <Button action="/example" method="POST" payload='{"fullName":"{exampleForm.fullName}","email":"{exampleForm.email}","notes":"{exampleForm.notes}"}' variant="outline" size="sm">
        Save draft
      </Button>
      <Icon name="sparkles" fallback="box" />
      <p>Cards, columns, and grid are no longer part of the XML surface.</p>
      <p>Quoted content renders as expected.</p>
      <p>Use p and standard content elements for layout.</p>
      <Button variant="outline" size="xs">Action</Button>
      <Button variant="ghost" size="sm">Archive</Button>
      <p>Details content appears in the default tab.</p>
      <p>Activity content shows an alternate view in the same section.</p>
      <p>Paragraph content explains how standard HTML elements render in XML pages.</p>
      <p>Unordered list items are no longer part of the XML surface.</p>
    </Query>
  </State>
</Page>
